The paper focuses on the temporal action proposal and localization tasks in the ActivityNet Challenge, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) fields. The proposed model is based on temporal convolutional network, which is a popular technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also mentions the accuracy of action classification, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
